            "heading": "The First Three Years: A Critical Development Window",
            "content": "<p>The first three years of life represent a critical window for skin development. During this period, the skin barrier, microbiome, and immune system are still maturing.</p><p>Understanding these early stages helps parents and caregivers make informed choices about skincare products and daily routines.</p>"
          }
        },
        "content_section_kejdeX": {
          "type": "content_section",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Influencing Factors",
            "content": "<p>Genetics, environment, diet, and skincare practices all play a role in how a child's skin develops during the first three years.</p><p>Gentle, microbiome-friendly products and minimal intervention support healthy barrier function without disrupting natural processes.</p>"
          }
        },
        "content_section_r8TaWR": {
          "type": "content_section",
          "settings": {
            "heading": "Sensitivity Reframing",
            "content": "<p>What may appear as sensitive skin is often a sign of an immature barrier still learning to regulate itself. Patience and gentle care are key.</p>"
